# HireWire — AI Coding Rules (Cursor)

## What this app is
Truth-based job application OS. Every generated document word is traceable to a real
evidence_library record. No hallucination, no inflation, no fabrication.

## Stack
Next.js 16 App Router · TypeScript · Supabase · Tailwind v4 · shadcn/ui · Vercel AI SDK v6

---

## Workflow Pipeline (NEVER bypass)
job_ingested → job_parsed → evidence_mapped → fit_scored → materials_generated → ready → applied

Stage derivation: lib/job-workflow.ts::getWorkflowState() — ONLY function for this.
Gate evaluation: lib/readiness.ts::evaluateJobReadiness() — ONLY function for gates.

job_parsed is TRUE when: job.qualifications_required.length > 0 OR job.responsibilities.length > 0
job.job_description is raw scraped text — NOT an analysis gate signal. Never use it as one.

---

## DB Backfill Rule
After analyzeJobCore completes, MUST write qualifications_required, responsibilities,
score, fit, score_gaps, score_strengths back to the jobs row (not only job_analyses).
Workflow functions read from jobs row directly — they never join job_analyses.

---

## Governance Hard Blocks (lib/coach/)
- Every bullet must cite a real evidence_library row (claim_validator.ts)
- Numbers may not exceed 2× the largest figure in cited evidence (drift-scorer.ts)
- drift.score >= 40 → HARD BLOCK (no DB write, 400 response)
- strategy = "do_not_generate" (coverage < 25%) → HARD BLOCK
- validateAllClaims() + scoreDrift() MUST run on every generation — never skip

---

## Tenant Isolation
Every Supabase query MUST include .eq("user_id", userId). No exceptions.

---

## UI Design System Classes
.hw-page .hw-workspace .hw-workspace-main .hw-workspace-rail
.hw-card .hw-panel .hw-btn-primary
.hw-stat .hw-stat-value .hw-stat-label
.hw-section-label .hw-empty .hw-next-action
Status badges: .status-draft .status-analyzing .status-ready .status-applied .status-offered .status-rejected

Design tokens: primary = #BD0A0A (Supreme Red), background = warm off-white #ede9e3

---

## Column Mapping (DB → TypeScript)
DB: role_title → Job.title (normalized in queries/jobs.ts)
DB: company_name → Job.company
Always use job.title / job.company in UI. Never job.role_title.

