## SightEngine — Operating Doctrine (v1.0)

SightEngine is the nervous system of HireWire. Not analytics — the system that answers:
what is happening, why, what should the user do next, what should the system learn, what changes downstream.

### The Closed Loop (every important action must follow this)
```
User action → Experience Layer captures → SightEngine logs event →
Intelligence interprets → Records updated → AI context enriched →
User gets better next step → Outcome tracked → Future recs improve
```

### 5 Design Rules (never violate)
1. Observe everything important, show only what matters
2. Every signal must have a reason (no scoreless warnings)
3. Every insight must have a next action (never show a gap without a CTA)
4. Don't turn analytics into noise
5. Product adapts quietly based on behavior

### Visual surface rules
- Dark surface → readiness score, recruiter signals, AI coach, risk warnings, package review, role intelligence
- Light surface → forms, job lists, onboarding, evidence editing, settings, general nav
- Red → primary actions, warnings, active signals, flagged gaps
- Green → verified evidence, completed steps, positive recruiter response
- Amber → moderate risk, missing proof, needs review
- Gray → inactive states, secondary metadata, helper text

### SightEngine Service Layer (canonical paths)
```
lib/sightengine/events/event-types.ts    — all event type constants
lib/sightengine/events/emit-event.ts     — emitSightEvent() client helper (never throws)
lib/sightengine/events/event-schema.ts   — SightEventInput type
lib/sightengine/ai/trace-ai-call.ts      — traceAiCall() — wraps every AI call
lib/sightengine/outcomes/record-outcome.ts — recordCareerOutcome()
lib/sightengine/insights/generate-insight.ts
app/api/sightengine/events/route.ts      — POST endpoint for client events
```

### Supabase tables (create IF NOT EXISTS, never destructive)
- sight_events — core event log
- sight_sessions — session tracking
- sight_ai_traces — AI reasoning metadata (no raw CoT)
- career_outcomes — real-world application results
- sight_insights — generated insights with lifecycle (active/dismissed/completed)
- feature_health — daily adoption rollup (unique on feature_key + date)

### Event type constants (grouped — use constants, never raw strings)
Session: SESSION_STARTED SESSION_ENDED USER_RETURNED USER_IDLE USER_REACTIVATED
Navigation: PAGE_VIEWED NAV_ITEM_CLICKED ROUTE_CHANGED BACK_NAVIGATION_USED MOBILE_MENU_OPENED
Onboarding: ONBOARDING_STARTED ONBOARDING_STEP_COMPLETED ONBOARDING_STEP_SKIPPED ONBOARDING_COMPLETED RESUME_UPLOADED TARGET_ROLE_ADDED
Jobs: JOB_IMPORTED JOB_PARSED JOB_VIEWED JOB_SAVED JOB_ARCHIVED JOB_DELETED JOB_STATUS_CHANGED
Role Intelligence: ROLE_ANALYSIS_STARTED ROLE_ANALYSIS_COMPLETED ROLE_REANALYZED ROLE_RISK_DETECTED
Evidence: EVIDENCE_CREATED EVIDENCE_UPDATED EVIDENCE_LINKED_TO_JOB EVIDENCE_USED_IN_RESUME EVIDENCE_GAP_DETECTED
Resume: RESUME_GENERATION_STARTED RESUME_GENERATED RESUME_EDITED RESUME_EXPORTED RESUME_MARKED_USED
Cover Letter: COVER_LETTER_GENERATED COVER_LETTER_EDITED COVER_LETTER_EXPORTED COVER_LETTER_MARKED_USED
Coach: COACH_OPENED COACH_MESSAGE_SENT COACH_SUGGESTION_ACCEPTED COACH_SUGGESTION_DISMISSED
Package: PACKAGE_STARTED PACKAGE_READY PACKAGE_REVIEWED PACKAGE_EXPORTED PACKAGE_SENT
Outcomes: APPLICATION_SUBMITTED RECRUITER_RESPONSE_RECEIVED CALLBACK_RECEIVED INTERVIEW_SCHEDULED INTERVIEW_COMPLETED REJECTION_RECEIVED OFFER_RECEIVED NO_RESPONSE_RECORDED
AI: AI_REQUEST_STARTED AI_REQUEST_COMPLETED AI_REQUEST_FAILED AI_OUTPUT_ACCEPTED AI_OUTPUT_REJECTED AI_GUARDRAIL_TRIGGERED AI_HALLUCINATION_PREVENTED
System: API_CALL_FAILED DATABASE_WRITE_FAILED AUTH_REQUIRED RATE_LIMIT_HIT

### AI trace rules
- Every AI call must call traceAiCall()
- Store: input_context_summary, output_summary, evidence_ids, confidence_score, guardrails_triggered, latency_ms
- Never store: raw chain-of-thought, full prompt dumps, unbounded AI output

### Insight rules (user-facing)
- Must be: short, actionable, explainable, non-judgmental, tied to evidence, dismissable
- Never: "Your applications are weak"
- Always: "This role asks for X but your resume does not show that clearly. Add one proof point."

### MVP implementation order
Phase 1: sight_events + emit helper + API route + page views + core events
Phase 2: sight_ai_traces + trace wrapper
Phase 3: career_outcomes + outcome UI + follow-up reminders
Phase 4: sight_insights + pattern detection
Phase 5: admin dashboard + feature health

### SightEngine never stores
Passwords, tokens, raw CoT, full prompt dumps, unnecessary PII, unredacted third-party secrets

---

## Never Do
- Compute workflow stage locally — use getWorkflowState()
- Use job.job_description as analysis gate
- Query without .eq("user_id", userId)
- Write requirements only to job_analyses — must backfill jobs row too
- Generate documents without evaluateJobReadiness() can_generate check
- Use localStorage for persistence
- Use useEffect for data fetching
- @apply a custom hw-* class inside another @layer components rule (Tailwind v4)
- Add banned phrases (results-driven, spearheaded, proven track record, etc.)
- Skip governance checks in generate-documents route

## Always Do
- requireUser() at top of every API route
- Await params/searchParams in Server Components (Next.js 16)
- "use client" on components with hooks or event handlers
- hw-* classes instead of re-implementing card/button/layout styles
- gap-* for spacing, never space-x-*/space-y-*
- Semantic tokens (bg-background, text-foreground) — never hardcoded colors
- Import Job/EvidenceRecord from lib/types.ts — no local duplicates
- console.error("[HireWire] ...") for all Supabase errors — never swallow silently

---

## Scoring System Quick Reference

Match score dimensions (lib/scoring-weights.ts):
- experience_relevance (0-50) — career alignment
- evidence_quality (0-40) — strength/specificity of proof
- skills_match (0-30) — technical skill coverage
- seniority_alignment (0-25) — level match
- ats_keywords (0-20) — keyword coverage

50 role profiles exist. Weights always sum to 100.
calculateWeightedScore(scores, roleProfile.weights) → final score

Evidence classification (lib/canonical-evidence.ts):
- direct_match — evidence directly proves requirement
- partial_match — partial coverage
- adjacent_transferable — related experience
- not_met — no evidence

---

## Coach System Quick Reference

Coach is AI conversational + tool-calling via AI SDK 6.

Session flow:
1. POST /api/coach/sessions → creates session with job/gap context
2. POST /api/coach/sessions/[id]/messages → streams response
3. POST /api/coach/confirm-tool-call → confirms evidence save
4. Domain event emitted → readiness recomputes

Key files:
- lib/coach/tool-execution.ts (998 LOC) — tool call handling
- lib/coach/claim-validator.ts — validates claims before save
- lib/coach/drift-scorer.ts — voice consistency drift
- components/coach-chat.tsx (576 LOC) — AI SDK chat UI
- components/coach/GapCoachDrawer.tsx (439 LOC) — per-gap modal

Coach sessions are ALWAYS scoped to (user, job, requirement).

---

## TruthSerum Provenance (lib/truthserum.ts)

Every generated bullet traces to real evidence.

Decision types: confirmed | skipped | auto_mapped | needs_judgment
Quality flags: weak_evidence | conflicting_sources | outdated | inferred

BulletTrace includes: evidence_id, decision_type, confidence, quality_flags

---

## Communications Registry (lib/comms/)

Centralized user-facing messages. Every message has a CommunicationReason.

COMMS_REGISTRY[messageId] → { id, reason, domain, channel, tone, title, body, actionLabel, actionHref }

Reasons: ACCOUNT_ACCESS | ONBOARDING_GUIDANCE | JOB_PROGRESS | GENERATION_QUALITY | APPLY_GATE

---

